A concept from architecture which is also used for online collaborative communities


'''Intimacy Gradient = organizing spaces in a sequence which corresponds to their degrees of privateness and openness'''


=Comment by Ross Mayfield=

URL = http://many.corante.com/archives/2003/12/22/think_group.php

"The ideal core/periphery structure affords a densely linked core and a dynamic perhiphery. One pattern for social software that supports this is an intimacy gradient (privacy/openness), to allow the core some privacy for backchannelling."

